<span id="freeTextContainer6632311396895974754">This story is captivating to say the least. Told through the eyes of a young Down syndrome woman, it bounces from the sometimes harsh real world around her to a surreal inner world with the guidance of her angelic friend Esther. Among many things that I noticed this novel addressed is our total misconceptions of what we consider weak and what we consider strong. Martin does a wonderful job of using this mostly non-verbal narrator to lay out the family dynamic with ease. It was a pleasure to read</span>
  <span id="freeText6632311396895974754" style="display:none">This story is captivating to say the least. Told through the eyes of a young Down syndrome woman, it bounces from the sometimes harsh real world around her to a surreal inner world with the guidance of her angelic friend Esther. Among many things that I noticed this novel addressed is our total misconceptions of what we consider weak and what we consider strong. Martin does a wonderful job of using this mostly non-verbal narrator to lay out the family dynamic with ease. It was a pleasure to read and I highly recommend it to anyone. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6632311396895974754" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

