<div id="review_974625385" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/974625385" />
    <a title="Michael Russel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32068610-michael-russel"><img alt="Michael Russel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1402153395p2/32068610.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/974625385?book_show_action=true">Jun 22, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Russel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Russel" href="/user/show/32068610-michael-russel">Michael Russel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer974625385" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8307396467106197903">Ordinarily, I shy away from books with plots surrounding war or warlike themes; I find the reality too painful for entertainment. Silver Mist&apos;s spiritual and metaphysical possibilities appealed to my curiosity; therefore, I threw the emotional caution to the wind.<br/><br/>The reader joins Eve on the day of her father&apos;s death. Esther arrives to stay with Eve while her family accompanies her father&apos;s body to Belfast. Esther&apos;s visit will be forever, unforgettable for Eve as she ventures through the metaphys</span>
  <span id="freeText8307396467106197903" style="display:none">Ordinarily, I shy away from books with plots surrounding war or warlike themes; I find the reality too painful for entertainment. Silver Mist's spiritual and metaphysical possibilities appealed to my curiosity; therefore, I threw the emotional caution to the wind.<br /><br />The reader joins Eve on the day of her father's death. Esther arrives to stay with Eve while her family accompanies her father's body to Belfast. Esther's visit will be forever, unforgettable for Eve as she ventures through the metaphysical.<br /><br />The characters are an interesting, delightful eclectic mix brought about by chance, in a situation reserved by those days akin to `Bloody Friday.' The premise of the story served as a reminder of the bloody massacre that seemed hidden behind more recent tragedies in my mind. I held this thought throughout the book...the author did his job well!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8307396467106197903" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


